            "text": "Day 4: Day Trip to Ayutthaya"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Morning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Take a day trip to Ayutthaya , the ancient capital of Thailand and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Start your visit at Wat Mahathat , famous for the Buddha head entwined in tree roots. Then, explore Wat Phra Si Sanphet , the largest temple complex in Ayutthaya."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Afternoon"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Enjoy lunch at a riverside restaurant, such as Krua Kao Suan , which offers traditional Thai dishes with a view of the Chao Phraya River. Afterward, visit Wat Chaiwatthanaram , a stunning temple with Khmer-style architecture, and take a boat tour along the river to see more ruins."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Evening"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Return to Bangkok in the evening and unwind with dinner at Supanniga Eating Room , a restaurant known for its elevated Thai comfort food. The cozy ambiance and riverside location make it a perfect spot to reflect on your day trip."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "Itinerary5": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Day 5: Modern Bangkok and Culinary Delights"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Morning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Start your day at Siam Square One , a contemporary shopping mall that doubles as a cultural hub. Explore rotating exhibitions, workshops, and events celebrating Thai creativity. For breakfast, try gourmet coffee and pastries at one of the mall’s trendy cafes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Afternoon"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Head to The Commons Saladaeng , a chic community space in the Saladaeng neighborhood. Enjoy lunch at one of its many restaurants, which range from casual eateries to fine dining options. Afterward, browse the boutique shops and art installations within the space."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 4,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Evening"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Conclude your trip with a memorable evening at Sky Bar at Lebua State Tower , one of Bangkok’s most iconic rooftop bars. Sip on creative cocktails while enjoying panoramic views of the city skyline. Pair your drinks with light bites and toast to an incredible five days in Bangkok."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stay tuned for the 7-day itinerary, which will include even more exploration of Bangkok’s neighborhoods, day trips, and immersive experiences!"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
